 to an incident where the Archangel Michael argued with the ___ over the body of Moses.","wiki"),("linus","5","A tomb that Torrigio discovered in Saint Peter's Basilica in 1615 and that was inscribed with the letters 'LINVS' previously was assumed to be the tomb of ___. However a note by Torrigio reveals that these were merely the final 5 letters of a longer name, e. g. 'Aqui___' or 'Anul___'. A letter on the martyrdom of Peter and Paul was once attributed to ___, but in fact it was determined to date to the 6th century. Absent evidence to the contrary, presumably the Liber Pontificalis is correct that ___ was buried on the Vatican Hill adjacent to Peter the Apostle in what is now the Vatican Necropolis beneath Saint Peter's Basilica in Vatican City, despite any absence of recent, corroborating evidence.","wiki"),("woman","5","The ___ gives birth to a male child who is threatened by a dragon, identified as the Devil and Satan, who intends to devour the child as soon as he is born. Frustrated, the dragon initiates war on 'the remnant of her seed', identified as the righteous followers of Christ.","wiki"),("books","5","Different religious groups include different ___ in their biblical canons, in varying orders, and sometimes divide or combine ___. The Jewish Tanakh . It is composed mainly in Biblical Hebrew, and its Septuagint is the main textual source for the Christian Greek Old Testament.","wiki"),("canon","5","A biblical ___ or ___ of scripture","wiki"),("creed","5","A ___  community in the form of a fixed formula summarizing core tenets.","wiki"),("right","5","The Christian ___ or the religious ___ are Christian political factions that are characterized by their strong support of socially conservative policies. Christian conservatives seek to influence politics and public policy with their interpretation of the teachings of Christianity.","wiki"),("sunni","5","Sunnī .","wiki"),("sects","5","___ of Sikhism are sub-traditions within Sikhism that believe in an alter