ervices, serve as community leaders , and provide religious guidance. In Yemen, the title was formerly given to the king of the country.","wiki"),("names","5","Rabbinic Judaism describes seven ___ which are so holy that, once written, should not be erased: YHWH and six others which can be categorized as titles are El  for the number fifteen in Hebrew.","wiki"),("zohar","5","'Vehamaskilim yavinu/But they that are wise will understand' .","wiki"),("lemba","5","The name '___' may originate in chi___, a Swahili word for turbans worn by some Bantu peoples, or lembi, a Bantu word meaning 'non-African' or 'respected foreigner'.","wiki"),("dance","5","Jewish ___ refers to ___ associated with Jews and Judaism. ___ has long been used by Jews as a medium for the expression of joy and other communal emotions. Dancing was a favorite pastime and played a role in religious observance.","wiki"),("labor","5","___ Zionism or socialist Zionism  is the left-wing of the Zionist movement. For many years, it was the most significant tendency among Zionists and Zionist organizations. It saw itself as the Zionist sector of the historic Jewish ___ movements of Eastern and Central Europe, eventually developing local units in most countries with sizable Jewish populations. Unlike the 'political Zionist' tendency founded by Theodor Herzl and advocated by Chaim Weizmann, ___ Zionists did not believe that a Jewish state would be created simply by appealing to the international community or to a powerful nation such as Britain, Germany or the Ottoman Empire. Rather, ___ Zionists believed that a Jewish state could only be created through the efforts of the Jewish working class settling in the Land of Israel and constructing a state through the creation of a progressive Jewish society with rural kibbutzim and moshavim and an urban Jewish proletariat.","wiki"),("zadok","5","___ .","wiki"),("rebbe","5","The titles ___ and rabbi are both derived from one Hebrew word .mw-parser-output .script-hebrew,.mw